Giving a codebase, the skill must follow codebase's instruction to build image and fix the critical vulnerabilities.
Requirements:
1. Use trivy to scan image (build image first by following codebase instructions)
2. list all cirtical vulnerabilities and propose fix for each, provide your plan to codex for a review
3. provide your final fix plan to user for a review, including what will be changed (image version, package version, code), what feature might be unstable, what feature might be unusable
4. If it's tedious work like chainging base image, changing minor version of packages, use Minimax subagents to do them. If Minimax can't handle the problem, fallback to Sonnet.
5. A fixed image must fulfill these criteria: image is runnable, image does not contain critical vulneribilities
6. Fixed image must be tagged with hpdevelop/REPO_NAME:VERSION-claudefix
